                        <summary> A manuscript copy of an illustrated guide to use of moxibustion
                            written in kanbun by Kagawa Shūan (1683-1755).</summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="ja" source="IANA">Japanese</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="Japanese_125">

                            <author key="person_24540504" source="VIAF">
                                <persName xml:lang="ja" source="IANA">香川, 修徳</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA">Kagawa Shūan</persName>
                                <note><p>Shūan spent some years in Kyoto studying Confucianism with
                                        the celebrated Itō Jinsai and the ‘Ancient School’ of
                                        medicine with Gotō Konzan, and he later became well known
                                        for his conviction that the roots of Confucianism and
                                        medicine were identical.</p></note>
